other_tests.findings: The liver is normal in size, echogenicity and architecture. The gallbladder is mildly distended and contains mobile shadowing gallstones. There is mild gallbladder wall edema. Sonographic ___ sign was not elicited. There is no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation, common duct measures 5 mm. There is normal hepatopetal flow in the main portal vein. There is no perihepatic ascites.
